<P>According to the date a&s;&s;igned to this tragedy, it is the fir&s;t drama extant in our language. In an Epi&s;tle prefixed to his patron Cannynge, the author thus cen&s;ures the MYS|TERIES, or religious interludes, which were the only plays then exi&s;ting.</P>
<Q><LG>
<L>Plaies made from HALLIE<NOTE N="i" PLACE="foot">Holy.</NOTE> TALES I hold unmete;</L>
