<PB REF="477">
a pau&s;e in a mid&s;t: ju&s;t as we chant the p&s;alms in our choral &s;ervice. In the p&s;alms of our liturgy, this pau&s;e is expre&s;&s;ed by a colon: and often, in tho&s;e of the Roman mi&s;&s;al, by an a&s;te|ri&s;c. The &s;ame mark occurs in every line of this manu&s;cript; which is a folio volume of con&s;iderable &s;ize, with upwards of fifty ver&s;es in every page.</P>
