<P>That is, <Q REND="inline">"Summer is coming: Loud &s;ing, Cuckow! Groweth &s;eed, and bloweth mead, and &s;pringeth the wood now. Ewe bleateth after lamb, loweth cow after calf; bullock &s;tarteth, buck <HI>verteth</HI> <NOTE N="g" PLACE="foot">Goes to harbour among the fern.</NOTE>: merry &s;ing, Cuckow! Well &s;inge&s;t thou, Cuckow, Nor cea&s;e to &s;ing now."</Q> This is the mo&s;t antient Engli&s;h &s;ong that appears in our manu&s;cripts, with the mu&s;ical notes annexed. The mu&s;ic is of that &s;pecies of compo&s;ition
