<P>Pag. 191. To Not. ^o. ADD, <Q REND="inline">"Another proof which a&s;cer|tains this reading of the controverted pa&s;&s;age in HAMLET, oc|curs in the romance of MORTE ARTHUR. When &s;ir Lancelo<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter"> was dying, <Q REND="inline">"whan he was <HI>how&s;eled</HI> and <HI>eneled,</HI> and had <HI>all that a cry&s;ten man ought to have,</HI> he praid the bi&s;hop, that his felowes might beare his bodie unto Joyous Garde, &amp;c."</Q> B. xxi. cap. xii.</Q></P>
