<P>Pag. 299. To the fir&s;t Note ADD, <Q REND="inline">"There is a manu&s;cript, Of a knight, called SIR OWEYN, vi&s;iting &s;aint Patrick's Purga|tory, Bibl. Bodl. MSS. BODL. 550. MSS. Cott. NERO. A. vii. 4. [See ad p. 199.] This piece was written by Henry, a Ci&s;tercian monk of Saltry in Huntington&s;hire. See T. Me&s;&s;ingham, FLORILEG.
